but here's the thing, is theaters didn't overprice their snacks and drinks, there wouldn't be incentive for people to sneak in outside candy.  For women it's easier as they often carry purses
But like I said
That's literally how they stay alive
The split of ticket sales is 80% (studio / distributor) 20% theater for the first 2 weeks or so, after which the theater starts to slowly get a bigger cut
But since the first 2 weeks drive the majority of sales, by the time the theater gets a good cut, nobody's seeing the movie at the same rate

If the studio's didn't take such a large portion of ticket sales, the price of concessions would likely come down by a noticeable amount, and this may happen in the near future, because those prices are driving people away
And if nobody goes to the theater to see the movie, the studios will keep getting less money until BOTH industries fail
The age old mantra of capitalism, "Adapt or die" :3
